        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): skip A2A announce flow in waited sessions_send path",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nClawSweeper review identified that the original fix unconditionally removed A2A announce for ALL waited sends, which broke normal peer waited sends. This fix narrows the skip to only the self/owned-child case (requester === target) where the inline reply is already delivered.\n\n**Key change**: `startA2AFlow` now only runs when `requesterSessionKey !== resolvedKey`, preserving A2A announce for cross-session (peer) waited sends while avoiding duplicate delivery for self-sends.\n\n## Changes\n- `src/agents/tools/sessions-send-tool.ts`: Add conditional guard for A2A flow in waited path\n- `src/agents/tools/sessions.test.ts`: Add two tests — self-send skips A2A, peer-send triggers A2A",
